 The scorched hillside around him appears utterly lifeless.
 Despain marvels at the tiny steps life is already taking to renew itself.
 His eyes red from the blowing ash, Mr.
 Despain patiently counts the quarter-inch lodgepole pine seed "wings" within a rectangular frame he places on the hillside.
 The little wings act like the rotary blades of a helicopter in dispersing the seeds. "This is amazing," says Mr.
